cirrhotic patients. On the contrary, its indications are decreasing for 
cirrhotics with the emergence of interventional therapies and since selected 
patients with small tumors and sufficient life-expectancy have become candidates 
to liver transplantation. Better results have to be obtained by adjuvant 
therapies in order to decrease the propension of the hepatocellular carcinoma to 
recur inside the liver. Intraarterial injection of lipiodol iodine-131 seems to 
give encouraging results in reducing the local recurrence rate after liver 
resection.

