Total joint replacement: a cost-effective procedure for the 1990s.

Hirsch HS(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Orthopaedics, Brown University School of Medicine, USA.

Total hip and knee replacement have been shown to be beneficial procedures not 
only by traditional clinical studies but by modern outcome measures as well. The 
cost-effectiveness of total joint arthroplasty compares favorably with 
non-surgical treatments for patients with advanced arthritis of the hip and 
knee. While cooperation is necessary among all participants in the health care 
